<p>Street lighting contractors sometimes follow road crews—brighter LEDs on smoother surfaces reduce glare hotspots that dazzled drivers on uneven patches. Small synergies like that multiply comfort without new budget lines if departments synchronize schedules.</p>

<h2>Looking ahead</h2>

<p>If the special fund and TURIP tranches converge as planned, Coimbatore could enter the next monsoon with fewer apology tours for cratered streets—provided utility agencies respect “dig once” discipline. The city’s reputation as an industrial and education hub deserves infrastructure that feels deliberate, not accidental. Asphalt alone cannot build that reputation, but without sound roads, little else works at the pace citizens expect.</p>

<p>Looking beyond statistics, the lived test is simple: can a parent push a stroller without mounting a kerb unexpectedly? Can a senior citizen cross at a zebra marking without sprinting? Can a loaded city bus turn without mounting a footpath? Kilometres on paper mean little if humane design fails at the corner shop.</p>

<p>Finally, night markets and late-hour eateries depend on deliveries; smoother last-mile surfaces reduce spoilage and driver fatigue—economic benefits that rarely appear in project cost-benefit sheets but show up in household budgets as lower vegetable prices and fewer broken crates.</p>

<h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>

